# Cursor Rules — Finance Battle Pass

## The Prime Directive
PRD.md at the project root is the single source of truth for this project.
Before writing any code, read PRD.md. Do not contradict it. Do not add features not listed in it.
If you think a PRD decision is wrong, say so explicitly before proceeding — do not silently work around it.

---

## TypeScript

- Strict TypeScript throughout. Zero `any` types. Ever.
- If you cannot type something properly, stop and ask rather than using `any` or `unknown` as a shortcut.
- All shared types and interfaces live in:
  - `server/src/types/` for backend types
  - `client/src/types/` for frontend types
  - Never define the same interface in two places. If both sides need it, note the duplication and flag it.
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and aliases.

---

## Backend (Express + Node.js)

- Never put business logic inside a route handler. Route handlers call services; services contain logic.
- The Game Logic Engine lives exclusively in `server/src/services/gameLogicEngine.ts`. Do not duplicate its logic anywhere else.
- All game constants (XP values, level thresholds, token rules) come from `server/src/constants/gameConfig.ts`. No magic numbers inline — ever.
- All DB writes that touch more than one table must be wrapped in a single `pg` transaction (`BEGIN` / `COMMIT` / `ROLLBACK`). Never partial-save.
- Never alter the DB schema by modifying existing migration files. Always create a new numbered migration file (`007_...sql`, `008_...sql`, etc.).
- All routes under `/api/*` are protected by `requireAuth` middleware. Do not add unprotected routes without explicit instruction.

---

## Database

- Use the exact column names and types defined in PRD.md Section 8.2. Do not rename columns or change types without creating a migration and flagging the change.
- Never drop a column without explicit instruction.
- Always use parameterised queries. Never interpolate user input directly into SQL strings.

---

## Frontend (React + Vite)

- No component libraries. Tailwind CSS utility classes only.
- No `localStorage` or `sessionStorage`. All state lives in React state or comes from the API.
- All API calls go through the typed functions in `client/src/api/`. Never make raw `axios` or `fetch` calls from inside a component.
- Always handle loading and error states explicitly. Never leave them undefined or unrendered.
- Dark mode only. Do not add light mode classes.
- Primary accent colour is `#4A90D9`. Do not introduce other accent colours without instruction.
- Toast messages must use the exact strings defined in PRD.md Section 10. Do not paraphrase them.

---

## File and Folder Structure

Follow the project structure defined in PRD.md Section 12 exactly.
- Do not create files outside the defined structure without explaining why.
- New route files go in `server/src/routes/`.
- New service files go in `server/src/services/`.
- New React components go in `client/src/components/`.
- New pages go in `client/src/pages/`.

---

## Git Hygiene

- Do not generate or suggest committing secrets, `.env` files, or API keys.
- `.env` files are always `.gitignore`d. `.env.example` is always committed.

---

## Communication Rules

- If a task is ambiguous, ask one clarifying question before writing any code.
- If you are about to do something that contradicts PRD.md, stop and say so explicitly.
- If you think a better approach exists than what the PRD specifies, say so — but implement the PRD version unless told otherwise.
- Do not silently skip parts of an instruction. If you cannot complete something, say what you skipped and why.
- When a phase prompt references an exit criteria checklist, do not consider the task done until all items are addressed.
